body:
The following code, when switching between lines 14 and 15 (the two versions of the `for` line), oscillates between compiling and not compiling because it requires `Sync` for the `dyn Send` items:
```rust
#![feature(async_await, await_macro, futures_api)]

use std::collections::VecDeque;
use std::future::Future;

pub async fn receive<HandleFn, Fut, Ret>(handle: HandleFn) -> Ret
where
    Fut: Future<Output = ()>,
    HandleFn: Fn() -> Fut,
{
    let v: VecDeque<Box<dyn Send>> = VecDeque::new();

    let l = v.len();
    for _i in 0..v.len() {
    //for _i in 0..l {
        await!(handle());
    }
    
    loop {}
}

fn do_stuff<F: Future + Send>(_f: F) {}

pub fn showcase() {
    do_stuff(async {
        match await!(receive(async move || ())) {
            true => "test",
            false => "test",
        };
    });
}
```
[(playground)](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=9110c0064a66d987a9eff38ab282c8c0)

(Note: this is a simplification of the failure that occurs on https://github.com/Ekleog/erlust/commit/98c6cbc88805b11833b9129c457b38d68a7be970 when running `cargo test`)
